\frametitle{Characteristics for advection}

$q(x,t) = \ico q(x-ut) \implies q$ is constant along lines 
\[
X(t) = x_0 + ut, \quad t\geq 0.
\]
Can also see that $q$ is constant along $X(t)$ from:
\begin{equation*} 
\begin{split}
\frac{d}{dt}q(X(t),t) &= q_x(X(t),t)X'(t) + q_t(X(t),t)\\
&= q_x(X(t),t)u + q_t(X(t),t)\\
&= 0.
\end{split}
\end{equation*}

